article.headline: E. Kentucky 73, N.C.-Asheville 54
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Mike Rose scored 24 points Saturday to lead Eastern Kentucky past North Carolina-Asheville 73-54. Rose hit four 3-pointers for the Colonels (4-1), who shot 51 percent for the game. Julian Mascoll added 13 points, while Jamaal Douglas had 10 and Michael Brock finished with a game-high 12 rebounds. James and Bryan Smithson scored 14 points each to lead the Bulldogs (1-4), who shot just 31 percent from the field and 22 percent from 3-point range. The Colonels ended the first half on a 6-0 run, ending with a running 3-pointer at the buzzer by Harrison Brown for a 31-21 lead. The Bulldogs narrowed the gap to 37-31 on a layup by Vincent James with 13:35 to play, but the Colonels hit six straight 3-pointers over the next five minutes to build a 55-39 lead. Eastern Kentucky led by as many as 22 points in the game. C.J. Walker became the Bulldogs' all-time leader in blocked shots in the first half, giving him 165 for his career.
